<exercise>
  <title>C4 - Homogeneous second-order linear IVP (ver. 86)</title>
  <statement>
    <p>Find the solution to the given IVP.</p>
    <me>y''+0y'-4y = 0 \hspace{1em} y(0) = 5 , y'(0) = -2</me>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>y= 2 \, e^{\left(2 \, t\right)} + 3 \, e^{\left(-2 \, t\right)}</me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
